<ul class="task-constraints">
<li><b>Time limit:</b> 1.00 s</li>
<li><b>Memory limit:</b> 512 MB</li>
</ul>
<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1747">
You are given an array consisting of $n$ distinct integers. On each move, you can swap any two adjacent values.<br />
<br />
You want to transform the array into a <i>pyramid array</i>. This means that the final array has to be first increasing and then decreasing. It is also allowed that the final array is only increasing or decreasing.<br />
<br />
What is the minimum number of moves needed?<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line has an integer $n$: the size of the array.<br />
<br />
The next line has $n$ distinct integers $x_1,x_2,\dots,x_n$: the contents of the array.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print one integer: the minimum number of moves.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 2 \cdot 10^5$<br />
<li>$1 \le x_i \le 10^9$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>4<br />
2 1 5 3</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>1</code><br />
<br />
Explanation: You may swap the first two values which creates a pyramid array $[1,2,5,3]$.    </div>
